_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_

**Migration reads storage before cleanup, so tag filter keys may still appear in initial state.**

The `local` and `session` variables are captured at lines 81-82 before the migration loop removes `includedTagFilters`/`excludedTagFilters` from storage. Since the returned state merges the original snapshots, any old tag filter keys will still be present in the initial state on first load after upgrade.

If the intent is to prevent localStorage tag filters from influencing initial state (per PR objectives), consider re-reading after migration or filtering the keys from the returned state.

<details>
<summary>🔧 Proposed fix to exclude tag filters from returned state</summary>

```diff
   getInitialState(base: State) {
-    const local = get(store.local);
-    const session = get(store.session);
-
